#Genre
Tragedy: human suffering
Comedy: amusement
- Parody: immitation
- Satire: social criticism
- Sarcasm/Irony: opposite meaning
Adventure
- Lost world: discovery of unknown
- Swashbuckler: ships and pirates
- Sword and sorcery: heroic fantasy
- Western: cowboys, guns
- Wuxia: chinese martial arts
Crime/Detective: solve mystery
Science fiction
- Apocalyptic: civilization collapse
- Dystopian: oppression
- Mecha: robots
- Space opera: interstellar
Romance: love story
Action
- Battle royale: competitive fight
- Spy fiction: secret missions
- Superhero: extraordinary powers
Folklore: traditional tale
- Fable: moral lesson, animals
- Fairy tale: magic, happy ending
- Legend: folk hero, historical
- Myth: gods, religious

#Narrative
Conflict
- Man vs Nature
- Man vs Man
- Man vs Society
- Man vs Self
Flashback: scene from past
Flashforward: scene from future
Rule of three
Far off places: only briefly describe remote places to keep the world bigger

#Hero's journey
Ordinary world
Call to adventure
Refusal of call
Meeting with mentor
Crossing the first threshold
Tests, allies and enemies
The ordeal
Reward
Return back

#Aarne–Thompson–Uther Index: folktale catalogue
1-299 = animals
300-749 = magic
: 300 = The Dragon-Slayer
: 310 = The Maiden in the Tower
: 328 = The Boy Steals the Ogre's Treasure
: 410 = Sleeping Beauty
: 440 = The Frog King

